  "text": "1 The uncertainties in the stress tensors were relatively small. The orientation of the s 1 axis was largely consistent with both the regional compressional strain rate axis as inferred from GPS data [CITATION_1] and the regional stress field [CITATION_2] . Curiously, the mainshock fault had a steep dip of 60°, which is far from favorably oriented for failure [CITATION_3] , considering that s 1 was nearly horizontal.",
